us throw]]\n* [[Javelin throw]]\n}}\n| event_type       = \n| universityteam   = \n| collegeteam      = \n| league           = \n| league_type      = \n| club             = \n| team             = \n| turnedpro        = \n| turnedpro_type   = \n| partner          = \n| former_partner   = \n| coach            = \n| retired          = \n| coaching         = \n| module2          = \n<!-- Achievements and titles -->\n| worlds           = \n| regionals        = \n| nationals        = \n| olympics         = \n| paralympics      = \n| commonwealth     = \n| highestranking   = \n| pb               = \n<!-- Medal record -->\n| show-medals      = \n| medaltemplates   = \n{{Medal|Competition| [[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold| [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]] | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's javelin throw|Javelin throw F54]] }}\n{{Medal|Competition| [[World Para Athletics Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver| [[2019 World Para Athletics Championships|2019 Dubai]] | [[2019 World Para Athletics Championships \u2013 Women's javelin throw|Javelin throw F54]] }}\n{{Medal|Competition| [[African Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold| [[Athletics at the 2015 African Games|2015 Brazzaville]] | Discus throw F54/57 }}\n{{Medal|Silver| [[Athletics at the 2015 African Games|2015 Brazzaville]] | Javelin throw F54/56 }}\n| medaltemplates-title = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Flora Ugwunwa''' (born 26 June 1984) is a Nigerian Paralympic athlete competing in [[T54 (classification)|F54]]-classification events.<ref name=\"paralympic_bio\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/flora-ugwunwa|title=Flora Ugwunwa|website=paralympic.org|url-status=live|access-date=22 December 2019|publisher=[[International Paralympic Committee]]}}</ref> She represented [[Nigeria at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]] and she won the gold medal in the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's javelin throw|women's javelin throw F54]] event.<ref name=\"paralympic_bio\"/> She also set a new world record of 20.25m at this event.<ref name=\"new_world_record_rio_2016\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.paralympic.org/feature/no-23-nigeria-most-successful-african-nation-rio-2016|title=No. 23 Nigeria most successful African nation at Rio 2016|date=9 December 2016|publisher=[[International Paralympic Committee]]|access-date=25 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShe qualified to represent [[Nigeria at the 2020 Summer Paralympics]] after winning the silver medal in the [[2019 World Para Athletics Championships \u2013 Women's javelin throw|women's javelin throw F54]] event at the [[2019 World Para Athletics Championships]] held in Dubai, United Arab Emirates.<ref name=\"world_para_2019_javelin_results_f54\">{{cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/dubai-2019/schedule/info-live-results/atdu19/eng/at/engat_athletics-results-women-s-javelin-throw-f54-1-01.htm |title=Dubai 2019 Results {{!}} Event Overview - Women's javelin throw F54|website=paralympic.org|url-status=live|access-date=25 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=flora-ugwunwa|old_id=1442153}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ugwunwa, Flora}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Paralympic medalists in athletics (track and field)]]\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of Nigeria]]\n[[Category:African Games medalists in athletics (track and field)]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2015 African Games]]\n[[Category:African Games gold medalists for Nigeria]]\n[[Category:African Games silver medalists for Nigeria]]\n\n\n{{Nigeria-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox 